timeline.bodyText:
I think you could use here a try-with-resources here to simplify the code a bit:
try (Partition root = SIDriver.driver().getTableFactory().getTable(table)) {
        return root != null ?  root.subPartitions(true).size() : 1;
} catch (Exception ioe) {
        throw StandardException.plainWrapException(ioe);
}

If I'm not mistaken the catch block will also catch an exception on root.close()

